Text.string: Lilith wants to see you on the bridge, recruit! You might think you're a big shot now that you rescued Tannis, but don't forget that I still outrank you! And I know where you sleep! Kidding not kidding! Bridge!
The Vault Hunter is here.
Waaaar paaaaath!
Welcome to the danger zone, punks!
Pedal to the metal. Just—step on the thing, with your foot! Just don't STOP!
Also, smashed spiderants are a bandit delicacy. Just sayin'.
We got more company! Keep our cargo safe!
Got a couple of new tails—let's chop 'em off!||I think I'm hungry.
More rigs incoming. Danger zone!
Whew, nice work. I think we're in the clear.
Pretty sure those other bandit settlements are abandoned.
Meant to do that.
I'm into it. Sorta. Ouch.
Whoo-hoo! I mean, ow! What the crap?
I'm okay, I'm okay!
Turrets! Turrets make me sad, ever since Troy Calypso phase-snatched mine. Let's give 'em hell!
Almost there!
Drive, bro, drive!
We're hit!
Takin' some lumps here, Vault Hunter.
We gotta fight back!
We got blasted!
They're shooting at us!
That's it. Blood feuuuuud!
We're takin' too much damage!
Not gonna last much longer!
We're getting shredded!
This thing's fallin' apart!
That thing does NOT enjoy being damaged.
That reactor does NOT like being damaged.
If we take any more damage, we are deep in skagsplatter!
While I appreciate alternative ways of thinking, uh, the car's wheels should probably be on the ground, bro!
Turn this car upside down!
No bueno! No bueno! Right us, bro!
We can't drive like this.
We made it! My blood is PUMPIN'! I love this planet! Go Sun Smashers!—I mean, Crimson Raiders! Woohoo!

I had intended to keep this a secret, but... best laid plans, robotic murder machine... well, you were there. And now the whole galaxy knows. I'm a star! See you back aboard Sanctuary, Vault Hunter. Oh, and... thank you. For the rescue.

Vault Hunter, bro. Heh, I gotta say—I've been on a lotta crazy roadtrips, but your driving skills? They're tasty, bro. They're tasty! So if you wanna ride sometime, you let me know, bro. Bro-adddd triiiip!
Whoa. Sorry. I, uh, got a little carried away there. Anyway...

We should deal with the matter at hand. Though the Vault Hunter cut off the Calypsos' pledge drive, they have already collected massive amounts of Eridium. They are preparing to use it for something. Perhaps to open the Great Vault.
Yeah, I'm with the Vault Hunter. What?
Now let's bro-chat!
I am merely addressing the evidence we have at hand. Lilith, if the Great Vault IS real, there must be a creature of incredible power within.
The Calypsos are already monsters, I don't want to see what happens if they steal that kind of power.
When I was taken, they held me at a stronghold where they were amassing all of their Eridium offerings. Whatever their plan entails, it will happen there.
Then that's where we strike. Killer, head down to Roland's Rest and tell Vaughn to rally the Raiders. We're ending this.
Eat my sculpted ass!
Skag off, you culty losers!
Keep on killin', Vault Hunter! You got this, bro. You got this! Bro...
Kill those COV bastards!
Murder! Murder! Murder!
Kill that freak!
You got this, bro. You got this, I think.
That abomination must DIE! But I must remain up here.
Go, bro, go! Kill kill kill kill! You you you you! Kill kill!
Hey, I hear we're launching an attack on the Calypsos' stronghold! It's about time! I'm all in, bro! I'm through bein' the Calypso's plaything. Bloood feuuuud!
Hear me, bros and bronettes! This is our moment. We're gonna ride to the Calypsos' gates and show those posers what happens when you mess with the Crimson Raiders!
Crimson Raiders, into the breach!
Ride, my Crimson army! Ride toward victory!
Let's do this!
You're attacking us? Are you serious? Eat turrets, you shitwaffles.
Ah, craps. I was wondering where those went.
Run, run, run, run, RUN! Everyone run!
Our tide! She has been turned!
Retreat to Roland's Rest! Fall back!
There you go! Happy hunting!
Now cross that skybridge. We must obtain my Eridium amplifier if we are to stand a chance against those turrets.
Now, caress the minecart. Just trust me on this one.
Ah, varkids. Their blood is nearly as corrosive as the average energy drink, and twice as caffeinated!
Down with the Calypsos!
Pesky things. Now, stroke my ex once more.

When my powers first manifested, it felt like a city's worth of electricity was coursing through my entire body. I laid my hand on a washing machine for balance and it instantly exploded. We were still finding loose socks weeks later. I realized I had no control over these new abilities, and I needed to find someplace where the only person I might accidentally kill was myself.
Try another switchboard. It's not receiving sufficient power.
Hey, bro—where you goin'?
Uh, bro! Come back! We—we gotta get this thing to Roland's Rest!
Yo, Vault Hunter. Where ya vaultin' to?
Hey, my Vault Hunter bro—we're sorta in the middle of somethin', ya know?
Oh boy, a COV drop ship! Watch out!
Aw, balls—the way's blocked. Shoot that watchtower!
Uh oh, way's blocked. Vault Hunter—shoot that tank!
Oh, crapzilla. We're gonna have to clear 'em out!
Take out those COV, Vault Hunter! We gotta get this Eridium who's-a-what's-it back to Roland's Rest!
Whoa, that technical looks decked out! Let's go smash it.
So, how's my ass look from back there?
Cardio liiiiife!
Hey, killer. Thanks for rescuing Tannis. Seems like no matter what happens, I can always count on you. I wanted to tell you, but—these days, being a Siren puts a target on your back.
Vault Hunter! You're here! We're under attack! Help!
Just in time, Vault Hunter! I thought we were goners!
Uh-uh-uh-uh, no—not so fast. Time to crush the Crimson Raiders once and for all! Tyreen, send in... Brayden.
I anoint thee: Ravager of Roland's Reacharound!
Whoo-hoo-hoo, Eridium! Hells yeah! Go forward and lay waste, my gladiator! Your soon-to-be-god commands it!
What the suck. It's a glower! Watch out!
Whoo, almost there!
Brayden! Agh, damn it. Nghh. Whatevers.
All right, that was scary! For you. Roland's Rest is safe! Ugh, it's about time we got a win.
That was... uh, weird. For everyone. Hey, maybe don't ask where I went. Ride, bro, ride!
Whoa! I'm back. Heh, y'know, for a second I thought I was back at Hyperion and it was all a dream, but... nevermind. Best not to ask too many questions. Let's ride, bro!
The mine's that way.
I knew Tannis was a Siren. She's been all up in my ship since I got here. Love ya, crazy T!
Wait—you sayin' the Great Vault actually exists?
Tannis... are you saying the Great Vault actually exists?
The Great Vault is real? Is that what you are implying?
The Great Vault isn't just a load of skag turds? It's real?
Blood feud!
Blood feud!
Blood feud!
Blood feud!
To the cathedral!
Later, Crimson traitors!

Well, that went real bad. But, as long as YOU survived, we still got hope, bro! So, anyway, and this is a little weird—uh, a ghost in my head told me you'd need help getting into the old Dahl mine? I'm into it. One sec!
My secret lab awaits! Go there now.

When my Siren powers first manifested, I knew I would need a covert area where I could experiment with them. Using an Eridium-based amplifier in the open would draw unwanted attention, and this abandoned Dahl mining operation provided a perfect cover.
The route's blocked, Tannis.
The route is blocked, Tannis.
The route is blocked, Tannis.
Route's blocked, Tannis.
Hmm... this way is also blocked. I suppose it is MY responsibility to walk you through each and every step. You must find a way to open those transport doors.
We are not in the clear! Let's fight 'em off!
Those doors may require some “Vault Hunter ingenuity”. Which is to say, you should start breaking things with reckless abandon. You do you!
Success! Ah, this remote domination is proving oddly satisfying. Oh, right. Lilith usually offers some affirmation! One moment.||Kudos. Yes, that will do nicely.
You're nearly there! But like everything and everyone on Pandora, it seems the elevator to my lab is irrevocably broken. You will need to find another way underground.
Double kudos! My lab isn't far now. As my professors often said, “you're making progress, now please put down the blowtorch.”
What's up? Slumming it in an abandoned mine. Okay, all right. I gotcha. Well, just wanted to let ya know that we are working on a—
Well, you won't get in that way. I hope you don't mind hoofing it, as they say. Do you have hooves? Honestly, most people are just a senseless collection of shapes and colors to me.
Thank you, Kate. We'll catch up soon. Now, Vault Hunter—the entrance is just down that corridor! You are nearly there!

You know, these derelict remains of my old employer's mine fill me with nostalgia! Ah, the good old days when I was an ambitious researcher, led only by limitless creativity and unbound by archaic concepts like ethics!
For the record, I never let ANYONE inside my lab, but for you I will make an exception. This time.
There it is. My Eridium amplifier! We'll need to bring it back to Roland's Rest. Disable those couplings to begin preparing it for transport.
Let's take those towers out, bro! Tower feuuuud! It's like a blood feud... but for towers!
Anyway, the Great Vault beckons! Later, superfan.
Excellent! Now, lower the amplifier. I believe one of those switches is more than up to the task.
You're looking for a saucy little minecart called Kate. She will show you the way. We had a brief and tumultuous affair that ended when our tracks went separate ways, as they say. Ah, so it goes.

Well done! I see why Lilith always sends you to do... well, everything. For now, we can install the amplifier in Roland's Rest. I've already instructed that human sculpture, Vaughn, to assist you in its transport. You can meet him in the garage downstairs.

Hey, Vault Hunter. So my head ghost told me to help you drive an Eridium whatever-dealy back to Roland's Rest for safekeeping. Still into it! Waiting for ya outside! No rush. I got some sweet tunes.||Oh, yeah, Digby Vermouth! Classic.
Hey, at least you remember your exes names. Ahhh... sometimes I miss old Blondie Number Two.
I get it. I was married for a while. Could have gone better. But, I guess I wouldn't be here saving the world if it had.
I am unfamiliar with organic courting rituals, so I cannot tell if you are being strange or not. I will assume this is typical.
Oh, I get it! No judgment here. I think I'm still married in seven different systems. Royalty in two!
Oh, shut up, Kate.
Varkids! Destroy them! If those things get into my lab, they could damage my precious equipment.
Ahhh, home crap home.
Man, I could take out towers for hours, but we gotta hurry!
Let's take down those cars and leave some scars!

We cannot reach the Calypsos' stronghold while those turrets are active. I might be able to shut them down with phaseshift, but for a task that large I will need my Eridium amplifier. It is in my secret lab hidden beneath an old Dahl mine nearby. Vaughn will show you the way.
Bro, what is it about old Dahl mines? Heh, am I right?
The lab entrance is in the large cavern. I'm not sure I can be more descriptive than that. It's a cavern, and it happens to be large.
All their vehicles must die! So says I, Vaughn!

We'll guard the Eridian flippity-floo and rally the troops. When Lilith gives the word, it's go time. Oh, and can you ask the lady-ghost-head-friend to stay out of my head from eight to eleven? That's where I keep the “special thoughts”.
I'VE got a big surprise for you! Huge reveal. You're gonna love it.
Destroy them! Let no vehicle escape our wrath!
Troy, come on. We talked about this.
You ready, bro? Let's do this!
No rush. Like I said, I got tunes.
I could listen to Digby Vermouth's velvet tones all day long, BUT, my head lady told me we gotta move this Eridium thinger-thing.
We should probably get on the road, right?
This thing's pretty important, right? I mean, probably wanna get it back to the base.
Yo, Vault Hunter. My trigger fingers are itchin' for some action! Or is that Pandora fever setting in? Either way, let's ride!
We gonna get goin' soon?
Come on, let's ride, bro!
Oh, fudge pants—the bandits found us! Drive, bro, drive!
Oh boy, spiderants. Hey, you're gonna wanna keep your distance! Those things are even uglier on the inside. Long story.
COV! Let's mess 'em up!
